This paper discusses the intersection of blockchain and IoT technologies, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the challenges of architecting blockchain-based IoT applications, which could fall under the categories of distributed, parallel, and cluster computing (cs.DC), software engineering (cs.SE), and data structures and algorithms (cs.DS).
